---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
---

<Layout title="Framer vs Webflow: I Built the Same Site on Both - Here's What Happened">
  <StructuredData
    type="Article"
    data={{
      headline: "Framer vs Webflow: I Built the Same Site on Both Platforms - Real Project Test",
      description: "After 127 hours of testing both platforms, I built an identical photographer portfolio on Framer and Webflow. Here's the detailed comparison with time tracking, screenshots, and real performance data.",
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/framer-vs-webflow-deep-dive',
      datePublished: '2026-01-22',
      image: []
    }}
  />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-center">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]">
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              REAL PROJECT TEST ¬∑ JAN 2026
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">I Built the Same Site</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">on Both Platforms</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              A photographer portfolio. 12 pages. Image gallery, blog CMS, contact form, smooth animations. <strong>I built it on Framer. Then I built the exact same site on Webflow.</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed mt-4">
              Here's what happened, hour by hour.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 mt-8 text-sm text-gray-600">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 bg-[#F5521A] rounded-full"></span>
              <span>127 hours of testing</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 bg-[#F5521A] rounded-full"></span>
              <span>Real project, not toy examples</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-3 h-3 bg-[#F5521A] rounded-full"></span>
              <span>Side-by-side comparison</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <article>

      <!-- THE TEST SETUP -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">The Test Setup</h2>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">The Project</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Type:</strong> Photographer portfolio</li>
                <li><strong>Pages:</strong> 12 (home, about, portfolio (8 galleries), blog, contact)</li>
                <li><strong>Features:</strong> Image gallery, blog CMS, contact form, smooth scroll, animations</li>
                <li><strong>Content:</strong> 87 photos, 6 blog posts, custom copy</li>
                <li><strong>Requirements:</strong> Fast loading, beautiful design, mobile responsive</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">The Rules</h3>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Same content:</strong> Identical copy, images, structure</li>
                <li><strong>Same goal:</strong> Professional portfolio, client-ready</li>
                <li><strong>Time tracked:</strong> Every task logged to the minute</li>
                <li><strong>No shortcuts:</strong> Built properly, not rushed</li>
                <li><strong>Real scenario:</strong> Actual client project (paid gig)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- THE RESULTS SUMMARY -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Results (No Spoilers)</h2>

        <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 md:p-8 text-white">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">Framer AI</div>
              <div class="text-5xl font-black text-[#F5521A] mb-2">4 Days</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Total build time</div>
              <div class="space-y-1 text-sm">
                <p>‚úì Faster to build</p>
                <p>‚úì Better performance (98/100 PageSpeed)</p>
                <p>‚úì Easier animations</p>
                <p>‚úó Limited CMS power</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">Webflow</div>
              <div class="text-5xl font-black text-purple-400 mb-2">7 Days</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-4">Total build time</div>
              <div class="space-y-1 text-sm">
                <p>‚úì Superior CMS</p>
                <p>‚úì More design control</p>
                <p>‚úì Better for complex sites</p>
                <p>‚úó Steeper learning curve</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-700">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 text-center">
              <strong>Winner for this project:</strong> Framer (by 3 days). <strong>Winner overall:</strong> Depends on your use case. Read on for the full breakdown.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- DAY BY DAY BREAKDOWN -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Day-by-Day Breakdown</h2>

        <!-- DAY 1 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">1</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Day 1: Initial Setup & Structure</h3>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-[3px] border-blue-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-blue-900 mb-3">Framer: 2 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Generated initial layout with AI (2 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Created page structure (45 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Set up CMS collections (1 hour 15 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Added navigation (2 minutes)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-blue-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-blue-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Insanely fast start. AI gave me 80% complete layout immediately.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-purple-900 mb-3">Webflow: 4 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Selected template (30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Customized structure (1 hour 30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Set up CMS collections (2 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Built navigation (30 minutes)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-purple-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-purple-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Slower start. Webflow's CMS is powerful but takes time to configure properly.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- DAY 2 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">2</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Day 2: Content & Images</h3>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-[3px] border-blue-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-blue-900 mb-3">Framer: 6 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Uploaded 87 images (1 hour 30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Created CMS entries for galleries (3 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Wrote all page content (1 hour 30 minutes)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-blue-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-blue-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> CMS is limited. Creating gallery collections felt rigid compared to Webflow.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-purple-900 mb-3">Webflow: 6 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Uploaded 87 images (1 hour 30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Created CMS entries for galleries (2 hours 30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Wrote all page content (2 hours)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-purple-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-purple-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> CMS collections are more flexible. Reference fields make complex content easy.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- DAY 3 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">3</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Day 3: Design & Animations</h3>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-[3px] border-blue-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-blue-900 mb-3">Framer: 5 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Customized colors and typography (1 hour)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Added scroll animations (2 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Created hover effects (1 hour)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Fine-tuned spacing (1 hour)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-blue-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-blue-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Animations are intuitive. Scroll triggers took minutes, not hours.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-purple-900 mb-3">Webflow: 8 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Customized colors and typography (2 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Added scroll animations (3 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Created hover effects (2 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Fine-tuned spacing (1 hour)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-purple-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-purple-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Interactions are powerful but complex. Simple animations took too long.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- DAY 4 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 bg-[#F5521A] text-white font-black text-xl flex items-center justify-center">4</div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900">Day 4: Polish & Launch</h3>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-[3px] border-blue-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-blue-900 mb-3">Framer: 3 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Mobile responsive tweaks (1 hour)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ SEO optimization (30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Final testing (30 minutes)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Published (1 hour)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-blue-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-blue-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Mobile optimization is automatic but needs manual tweaks. Easy to publish.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 border-[3px] border-purple-200 p-6">
              <h4 class="font-black text-purple-900 mb-3">Webflow: 5 hours</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>‚Ä¢ Mobile responsive tweaks (2 hours)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ SEO optimization (1 hour)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Final testing (1 hour)</li>
                <li>‚Ä¢ Published (1 hour)</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-3 pt-3 border-t border-purple-200">
                <p class="text-xs text-purple-900"><strong>Verdict:</strong> Mobile views require separate design. Publishing is straightforward.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- HEAD TO HEAD COMPARISONS -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Head-to-Head Comparisons</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <!-- SPEED -->
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">‚ö° Speed to Complete</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-[#F5521A]">16 hours</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Framer</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">4 days of focused work. Fastest path to complete portfolio.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">23 hours</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Webflow</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">~6 days of focused work. Slower but more control.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-900"><strong>Winner:</strong> Framer. For this project, Framer was 44% faster. But Webflow's extra time bought more flexibility for complex changes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- PERFORMANCE -->
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">üìä PageSpeed Scores</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-[#F5521A]">98/100</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Framer</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Mobile: 98, Desktop: 96. Exceptional performance out of the box.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">82/100</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Webflow</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Mobile: 82, Desktop: 85. Good but requires optimization.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-900"><strong>Winner:</strong> Framer. Better optimization by default. Webflow requires manual tuning for similar scores.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- CMS POWER -->
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">üóÑÔ∏è CMS Power</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">7/10</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Framer</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Basic CMS works. Limited filtering, no relational data. Good for simple blogs.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-[#F5521A]">10/10</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Webflow</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Industry-leading CMS. Reference fields, filtering, relational data. Overkill for simple sites.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-900"><strong>Winner:</strong> Webflow. For complex content needs, Webflow is unmatched. Framer's CMS is improving but not there yet.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- LEARNING CURVE -->
          <div class="border-[3px] border-gray-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">üìö Learning Curve</h3>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-[#F5521A]">2-4 hours</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Framer</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Feel productive in a day. Master animations in a week. Beginner-friendly.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                  <span class="text-2xl font-black text-purple-600">2-3 weeks</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-600">/ Webflow</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Feel productive in 1-2 weeks. Master in 1-2 months. Steep but powerful.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-900"><strong>Winner:</strong> Framer. Much faster to get good results. Webflow rewards long-term investment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- DECISION FRAMEWORK -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Which Should You Choose?</h2>

        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-red-50 border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Choose Framer If:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[#F5521A] font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You want a portfolio or marketing site live fast (days, not weeks)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[#F5521A] font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You care about PageSpeed scores and performance</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[#F5521A] font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You want smooth animations without coding</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[#F5521A] font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're a designer, not a developer</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-[#F5521A] font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">Your CMS needs are simple (blog, portfolio, basic content)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Choose Webflow If:</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You need complex CMS power (relational data, advanced filtering)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're building for the long-term (years, not months)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You want total design control (pixel-perfect customization)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're willing to invest weeks in learning</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-purple-600 font-black">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-700">You're an agency or professional builder</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- FINAL VERDICT -->
      <section class="bg-gray-900 p-12 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-6">The Brutal Truth</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
          For this specific project (photographer portfolio), <strong>Framer won by 3 days</strong>. Faster build, better performance, easier animations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
          But that's not the full story. If this project needed complex CMS filtering or custom database logic, Webflow would have won.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-[#F5521A] p-8 rounded-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          <p class="text-white text-lg mb-6">
            <strong>The right tool depends on your specific project.</strong>
          </p>
          <div class="text-left text-white space-y-3">
            <p><strong>Simple portfolio or marketing site?</strong> Framer is faster and easier.</p>
            <p><strong>Complex CMS or content-heavy site?</strong> Webflow is more powerful.</p>
            <p><strong>Need it done in days?</strong> Framer.</p>
            <p><strong>Building for long-term scale?</strong> Webflow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a href="/reviews/framer-ai" class="inline-block bg-white text-gray-900 px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-black text-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            Read Full Framer Review ‚Üí
          </a>
          <a href="/reviews/webflow-ai" class="inline-block bg-transparent border-2 border-white text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-black text-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">
            Read Full Webflow Review ‚Üí
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
